Maintained as control nematodes but passed with an applied voltage (bio-electrosprayed).  Bio-electrospraying was carried out with a stainless steel needle with an internal and external bore diameter of ~6 and ~8mm respectively. The mid-section of the needle, held firmly in resin, was connected to a high voltage power supply (FP-30, Glassman Europe Ltd, Tadley, UK) capable of providing a voltage of up to 30kV with a drawing current of ~4mA with high resolution. The inlet of the needle was connected to medical grade silicone tubing with a similar internal bore diameter. The inlet end of the silicone tube was connected to a reservoir of M9 buffer containing age synchronous C. elegans larvae (L1s). The flow of suspended nematodes was controlled by way of gravitational flow and could be varied from ~10-5-10-8m3s-1.
